The prototypical hybrid or semi-flow RFB is the zinc/bromine system [60]. In this system, electrolyte solutions containing the reactive species are stored in external tanks and circulated through each cell in the stack, but the zinc reaction does not only involve dissolved species in the aqueous phase. At the positive electrode, bromide ions are transformed to bromine and back, see Eq. 5. It is important to note that the bromide ions can combine with bromine molecules to generate the tribromide ion [61]11\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
