				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ Sh = 14.29Re^{ 0. 3 4 8} $$\end{document}This functional dependence on Re is in excellent agreement with Sioda’s [127] and Cano and Bohm’s [128] findings.

Since most IEMs are single ion conductors (see Table 3), transport within them can often be described using Ohm’s law (Eq. 27). If there are other interactions such as electroosmotic flow, this description can be modified; for example, for proton conduction in Nafion® the following expression can be used [139, 140]35\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
